The paper focuses on a new dataset for visual reasoning and question answering, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new question engine and metrics for evaluating models, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the dataset and models are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) as they involve understanding and reasoning about real-world scenes.
